11/3/2025 \uD83C\uDF31 Community Garden.Name: 11/3/2025 🌱 Community Garden Expansion Our community garden is growing—literally! We’ve added new planter boxes and fruit trees. Residents interested in gardening can sign up for a plot at the clubhouse.

13/4/2025 \uD83D\uDCE2 New Playground In.Name: 13/4/2025 📢 New Playground Installed! Great news for families! A brand-new playground has been installed at the community park, featuring swings, slides, and a shaded seating area. Bring your kids and enjoy the upgraded space!

2/3/2025 \uD83D\uDC3E Pet Park Rules Upd.Name: 2/3/2025 🐾 Pet Park Rules Update To ensure a safe and enjoyable environment, all pets must now be leashed when entering and exiting the dog park. We also encourage pet owners to use the provided waste disposal stations—let’s keep our park clean!

20/2/2025 \uD83D\uDEA8 Extra Security fo.Name: 20/2/2025 🚨 Extra Security for Peace of Mind! We’ve added more CCTV cameras around the entrance and parking area. Let’s keep our community safe—if you see anything unusual, give management a heads-up!

20/3/2025 \uD83D\uDEE0 Clubhouse Renovat.Name: 20/3/2025 🛠 Clubhouse Renovations The community clubhouse is undergoing a much-needed facelift. Improvements include new flooring, fresh paint, and upgraded furniture. The clubhouse will be closed until April 20—thank you for your patience!

3/4/2025 \uD83D\uDEB4 Bike Lanes Coming.Name: 3/4/2025 🚴 Bike Lanes Coming Soon Exciting news for cyclists! The city has approved plans to add dedicated bike lanes near our community. Construction will begin in May and is expected to be completed by the end of the year.
